  <description><![CDATA[<p>Located on Wengens main street, the Residence Bernerhof Apartments give you excellent access to the incredible Jungfrau ski area. The comfortable studio apartments are a great choice if you are looking for self-catered apartment style accommodation in <a data-udi="umb://document/52fab17731fa49639f8a0841e064a064" href="/{localLink:umb://document/52fab17731fa49639f8a0841e064a064}" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a>.</p>
<h2>Central location</h2>
<p>These studios and apartments offer comfortable accommodation in the charming centre of Wengen. The location couldn't be better, the apartments are just a four-minute walk the Männlichen gondola which gives you access to <a data-udi="umb://document/f6cb1f0178b7447488bbf36b5f109fbc" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f6cb1f0178b7447488bbf36b5f109fbc}" title="Grindelwald">Grindelwald</a> and the slopes of the Jungfrau Ski Region. The train station is about a four minute walk away where you can head up to the Top of Europe, or if you fancy a day off from skiing head down to the picturesque Lauterbrunnen. </p>
<h2>Self-catered apartments</h2>
<p>These self-catered apartments each have a well-equipped kitchenette, seating area and recently renovated bathrooms. You can also enjoy wonderful views over the valley towards Murren from your private balcony or terrace.</p>
<p>Take the fuss out of breakfast and upgrade your stay to Bed &amp; Breakfast. Each morning breakfast is served in the Hotel Bernerhof, you can get prepare for a day on the slopes at the breakfast buffet which includes a range of homemade jams and preserves, muesli, cereals, local cheeses and cold cuts. </p>
<p>If you don't feel like cooking, head to the Taverne at the Hotel Bernerhof for delicious Swiss specialties including cheese or meat fondue, röstis or raclette. If you are cheesed out, there is also a range of homestyle dishes.</p>]]></description>
